{
  "page": "Did you know/94",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>... that <a href=\"/index.php/House_Jordayne\" title=\"House Jordayne\">House Jordayne</a> of the <a href=\"/index.php/Tor\" title=\"Tor\">Tor</a> refers to the late fantasy author <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Robert_Jordan\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Robert Jordan\">Robert Jordan</a>, whose <i><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wheel_of_Time\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Wheel of Time\">Wheel of Time</a></i> series is published by <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tor\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Tor\">Tor</a>?<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> The name of the ruling Lord of the Tor at the start of the series is <a href=\"/index.php/Trebor_Jordayne\" title=\"Trebor Jordayne\">Trebor</a>, which is \"Robert\" spelled backwards.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Did_you_know/94&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">The Citadel: <a class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.westeros.org/Citadel/FAQ/Entry/Are_there_any_nods_to_other_works_in_the_series\">Are there any nods to other works in the series?</a></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260405223655\nCache expiry: 1209600\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.007 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.008 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 33/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 190/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 114